  <h1>Ontology — the authoritative reference</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    The published, generated reference of the OPDA PDTF ontology itself — the canonical
    specification to link people to. Everything here is generated from the committed TTL
    corpus at <code>source/03-standards/ontology/</code> and guarded by the doc-drift CI gate,
    so it cannot silently diverge from the model. This page is the entry point; the cards
    below lead into every layer of the reference.
  </p>

  <nav class="callout callout--note" aria-label="On this page">
    <div class="callout__label">On this page</div>
    <ul style="margin: 0;">
      <li><a href="#combination">The combination principle</a></li>
      <li><a href="#counts">Live headline counts</a></li>
      <li><a href="#explore">Explore the reference</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <h2 id="combination">The combination principle</h2>
  <p>
    No single off-the-shelf tool documents the whole ontology — the OWL generators skip SHACL
    and treat SKOS unevenly, and none render the OPDA-specific layers at all. So this reference
    is one <strong>woven composition</strong> of three methods (ADR-0041):
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Tool renderings</strong> — the best off-the-shelf tool per layer (pyLODE / WIDOCO for OWL, SHACL Play! for shapes, Ontospy / Skosmos for SKOS), scored in the <a href="/ontology/bake-off">bake-off</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Custom <code>opda-gen</code> scripts</strong> — the OPDA-specific layers no tool covers: the overlay profiles + GAP register, the round-trip exemplars, and the three-graph separation.</li>
    <li><strong>LLM-authored prose</strong> — the conceptual / governance layer a generator cannot emit: <em>why</em> the model is shaped as it is, the decision provenance, and the known-issues register.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Redundancy with neighbouring sections is intended and fine (ADR-0041 rev-3, M1) — this
    section is designed standalone. For <em>how</em> the model was built see
    <a href="/modelling">Modelling</a>; for the DAMA four-tier reader presentation see
    <a href="/model">Model</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="callout callout--warn">
    <div class="callout__label">Status — draft, under review</div>
    <p>
      The PDTF-to-ontology programme is <strong>RETIRED 2026-06-14</strong> (a historical
      anchor; modelling continues under fresh ODRs). This reference carries
      <code>status: draft</code> until the doc-drift CI gate is green and the operator settles
      the per-layer pick (ADR-0041 M6). See <a href="/ontology/provenance">Decision
      provenance</a> for the full retirement and ratification record.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="counts">Live headline counts</h2>
  <p>
    Read at build time from the committed TTL corpus — these numbers cannot drift from the
    model without failing the doc-drift gate.
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Layer</th><th>Live count</th><th>Source</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>OWL classes</td><td>{counts.classes}</td><td>module TTLs (asserted <code>owl:Class</code>)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Object properties</td><td>{counts.objectProps}</td><td><code>owl:ObjectProperty</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Datatype properties</td><td>{counts.dataProps}</td><td><code>owl:DatatypeProperty</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>SKOS concept schemes</td><td>{counts.schemes}</td><td><code>opda-vocabularies.ttl</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>SKOS concepts</td><td>{counts.concepts}</td><td><code>opda-vocabularies.ttl</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>SHACL base node-shapes</td><td>{counts.shapes}</td><td><code>*-shapes.ttl</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Overlay profiles</td><td>{counts.profiles}</td><td><code>profiles/*.ttl</code> (most thin by design)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Round-trip exemplars</td><td>{counts.exemplars}</td><td><code>exemplars/*.ttl</code> (scenario inputs)</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="muted tiny">
    Profiles are mostly <strong>thin by design</strong> — they bind Category-G leaves only, and
    GAP-register the rest (224 bound / 1095 GAPped at session-034). See
    <a href="/ontology/known-issues#thin">Known issues</a> for why that is the ratified outcome,
    not an omission. Downloadable TTL bundles are on <a href="/ontology/usage#downloads">Consume
    the ontology</a>.
  </p>

